('Amar Singh Chamkila', 'Amar Singh Chamkila, often referred to as the “Elvis of Punjab,” was a legendary Punjabi singer, songwriter, and musician. Born in 1960 in Punjab, Chamkila revolutionized Punjabi music during the 1980s with his raw, relatable, and sometimes controversial lyrics. His songs covered a wide range of themes, from romance and cultural pride to social issues and the daily struggles of common people. Despite criticism for addressing taboo subjects, his fearless songwriting and infectious melodies made him a household name. Chamkila, along with his wife Amarjot, performed extensively across Punjab, attracting massive audiences. Tragically, his life was cut short in 1988 when both were assassinated, leaving behind an enduring legacy. Today, Chamkila is remembered as an icon whose bold artistry continues to influence Punjabi musicians. His songs are still celebrated, covered, and sampled, proving his unmatched impact on the music landscape.', '1960-07-21', 0),
